subtitleNullable: The Daily Air Quality Index (AQI) in Jakarta from 2010 - 2021
descriptionNullable:
This dataset contains the Air Pollutant Standard Index (AQI) or Indeks Standar Pencemar Udara (ISPU) as measured from 5 air quality monitoring stations (SPKU) in DKI Jakarta since 2010 until 2021

Explanation of variables from the data above as follows:

1. tanggal : Date of air quality measurement
2. stasiun : Measurement location at the station
3. pm10 : Particulate matter one of the measured parameters
4. pm25 : Particulate matter one of the parameters measured
5. so2 : Sulfide (in the form of SO2) one of the parameters measured
6. co : Carbon Monoxide one of the parameters measured
7. o3 : Ozone is one of the measured parameters
8. no2 : Nitrogen dioxide one of the parameters measured
9. max : The highest measured value of all parameters measured at the same time
10. critical: The parameter with the highest measurement results
11. category : Category based on the calculation of the air pollution standard index

This data is taken from Open Data Jakarta where the data source comes from the DKI Jakarta Province Environmental Service.
